    <item>
      <title>First Proof: Sum of First n Integers</title>
      <link>https://angelo-blog.github.io/posts/first-proof/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 25 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://angelo-blog.github.io/posts/first-proof/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;We prove:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$$
1 + 2 + \cdots + n = \frac{n(n+1)}{2}
$$&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;proof&#34;&gt;Proof&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We use induction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Base case: n = 1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$$
1 = \frac{1 \cdot 2}{2}
$$&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hence true.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inductive step:
Assume true for n, prove for n+1.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
